OL,3,CWarning from Devon man left paralysed
OL,4,Cin drink driving crash
OL,6,FA man from Devon paralysed in a drink
OL,7,Fdriving crash has warned people "don't
OL,8,Fmake the wrong decisions".
OL,10,FBack in 2022 Seth Marks, who was 18 at
OL,11,Fthe time, was out drinking with
OL,12,Ffriends.
OL,14,FAt the end of the night, Seth got into
OL,15,Fa friend's car and didn't put his
OL,16,Fseatbelt on.
OL,18,FWhat followed was a high speed crash
OL,19,Fthat left Seth paralysed. The force of
OL,20,Fthe crash snapped the back of his neck
OL,21,Fand damaged his spinal chord.
